metadata.name: alchemy(maxima) #14
metadata.description:
This collection takes its main inspiration from the Turkish marbling art “Ebru” and tries to spin it with a golden twist, hence alchemy :) 

alchemy(maxima) tries to create a composition either using one of the two grid types, and sometimes breaking them or in a totally chaotic way, but uses color harmony and rhythm to keep the chaos in check and the resulting image still somewhat interesting and sometimes golden-ish…

The name includes “maxima” because this is the first part of a 2-part series; its companion collection “alchemy(minima)” will be released soon and as per my tradition will be freely available to maxima holders.

From the proceeds of the primary sales of alchemy(maxima),

- 33% will directly go to The Processing Foundation,
- 33% will fund the greater evil,
- 34% will be used to grow my collection.

So in a way, all the proceeds will go back into the ecosystem. This is my way of making up for taking tez out with my donations earlier.

If you are wondering what the hell “the greater evil” is, read about it here : 

https://twitter.com/evilnft/status/1544320804304961536?s=20&t=AoEfLfn32tGNR8JTi5Jjng

And find it here:

https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/the%20greater%20evil/collection

—

About the work: 

- 22 palettes - 7 new, 15 recycled,
- 3 main variants,
- 4 sub-variants each,
- 9 visible and some hidden features :)
- After going live, press “s” to save a png (at your screen resolution)
- No hi-res output due to the warp manipulating the pixel array directly, which means higher res equals to much higher computation time.

Thank you all in advance and have a good day!

Warp functions are based on this article by Inigo Quilez : https://iquilezles.org/articles/warp/

DISCLAIMER : I am not a good coder, I have tried to fix my past mistakes from my earlier projects to make some room for new mistakes :) I am learning on the way and certainly hoping that there aren't any huge bugs or anything, so you can enjoy your mint! Please hit me up if you have any concerns after minting and we can discuss a solution.

metadata.description: BEARHEAD's Vampire Punchers is a generative collection based on the novella series - Vampire Punchers. In a world where vampires spread abroad - high schools train teams of cheerleaders to stop these blood sucking fiends for sport and school spirit.

metadata.name: The dice is cast #23
metadata.description:
When I started studying the code and learning the "random" functions in early July 2022, it made me think of randomness when throwing dice. It is random, but with these restrictions (3 six-sided dice = 216 possibilities). 

With this mindset and theme, I began to create this first attempt at generative art. 

In my usual work, I take everyday objects, materials, etc. and play with them. For this series, I inserted blocks of polystyrene to give it substance. 

All the graphic elements, colours and random arrangements were created using P5.js. The photos of polystyrene and the dices are integrated.

Press ENTER to download as a jpg image. 

@Yomu Oyashi July 2022

The NFT licence 2.0

metadata.name: DisOrder #4
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 84 · 56 · 38 · 26 · 18  every 8 minutes.
Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

All that is, starts with Order.

Order attempts to evade entropy by following its own intrinsic patterns. Then, inevitably, there is change: an anomaly, a nudge that turns into a catalyst for widespread change.The momentum cannot be stopped.

Brief cycles build upon themselves, iterating and breaking into something new with each turn. Now, looking back, the accumulation of small divergences look like a leap, with trails of evolutionary decline casting tall shadows on the patterns that bore them.

The beauty of what this entropy creates, rises beyond chaos. It represents the past, and signals the future, and suddenly looks like a wild take on Order itself – the true DisOrder of life.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

FEATURES :
21 Features implemented including colors, styles, technical parameters...

INTERACTIVITY :
Press ‘h’ in live mode for a list of options.
Press 's' to save an image of the output at the current resolution
Press ‘1’-’9’ to increase resolution
...
